You are adding TEI XML to textual notes for the plays of Aeschylus, one play at a time. You will use your judgment in most cases.

Notes will be of the form:

NUMBER. GREEK SOURCES

The input:

2. ναῖον ἀρόεντ' Μ. G. P. Rob. ναῖον ἀρόεντα Ε. in margine,
quum omissa essent in textu. νάϊον ἀρθέντα Turn. Coniungenda esse
νάϊον ἀρθέντα non monerem, nisi lapsos quosdam viderem in re aper-
tissima.
3. ἀπὸ προστομίων Μ. in quo inter π et o in ἀπό aliquid era-
et Rob. ἀποστομίων G. πρὸ στομίων Turn. Dubitari potest

becomes:

<p><bibl n="2">2.</bibl> <lem xml:lang="grc">ναῖον ἀρόεντ'</lem> Μ. G. P. Rob. <quote xml:lang="grc">ναῖον ἀρόεντα</quote> Ε. in margine,
quum omissa essent in textu. <quote xml:lang="grc">νάϊον ἀρθέντα</quote> Turn. Coniungenda esse
<quote xml:lang="grc">νάϊον ἀρθέντα</quote> non monerem, nisi lapsos quosdam viderem in re apertissima.</p>

<p><bibl n="3">3.</bibl> <lem xml:lang="grc">ἀπὸ προστομίων</lem> Μ. in quo inter π et o in <foreign xml:lang="grc">ἀπό</foreign> aliquid eraet Rob. <quote xml:lang="grc">ἀποστομίων</quote> G. <quote xml:lang="grc">πρὸ στομίων</quote> Turn. Dubitari potest